# After Plugin System

- Do not fork the app shell for optional features. Contribute via
  `AfterPluginManifest` / `AfterPluginRegistry`.
- Load catalogs with `hydrateAfterPlugins` from `assets/plugins/catalog.json`
  and/or Remote Config key `after.plugins.catalog`.
- Supported contributions: `page`, `dashboardWidget`, `aiSkill`, `report`,
  `form`, `api`, `navigationItem`, `businessModule`.
- Shell reads `afterPluginNavigationItemsProvider` /
  `afterPluginPagesProvider` / `afterPluginAiSkillsProvider` — never
  hard-code plugin routes in core.
- Use `AfterPlugin.install` only for executable handlers on `AfterPluginHost`.
- Merge dashboard tiles with `applyPluginDashboardWidgets`.
- Docs: `docs/PLUGIN_SYSTEM.md`. Examples: `examples/plugins/`.
